        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "The COVID-19 pandemic has forced us to consider the physiologic role of obesity in the response to infectious disease . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "There are significant disparities in morbidity and mortality by sex , weight and diabetes status . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "Numerous endocrine changes might drive these varied responses to SARS - CoV-2 infection",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "including hormone and immune mediators , hyperglycemia , leukocyte responses , cytokine secretion , and tissue dysfunction . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "Studies of patients with severe COVID-19 disease have revealed the importance of innate immune responses",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "in driving immunopathology and tissue injury . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this review we will describe the impact of the metabolically induced inflammation ( meta - inflammation )",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that characterizes obesity on innate immunity . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "We consider",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that obesity - driven dysregulation of innate immune responses may drive organ injury in development of severe COVID-19 and impair viral clearance . <S> <P>",
